<br>
Iam a student writing a report on the Vietnam war and the effects that it had on those that fought in it ( the vets ). I have read your comments about this Dr. Spatz and I fully disagree with what he had to say. The men that fought in the Vietnam war were heroes. Maybe not the kind that we picture in every day life (e.g. Prince Charming ) but they were heroes in a sense that their country called on them and they listened. They had to suffer through more tragedy than I will ever experience in my lifetime and I respect them for their courage.Vietnam was one of the most gruesome wars of all time and any human being that went through it deserves more than I can ever say. I know all this because someone close to me has made their experience in the war very real in my life. My best to all of you and God bless.
<p><code>--   (An Observer) </code><p>


